---
layout: base.njk
title: Web Everything - Demos
---

{% from "project-status.njk" import projectStatus %}

{% set showcases = demos | rejectattr("kind", "equalto", "playground") %}

<div class="page-header">
    <h1>Demos</h1>
    <p class="page-description">
        Web Everything protocols in real action — compelling, real-usage showcases that integrate multiple
        standards into working experiences. Looking for headless proofs that a standard is satisfied? Those
        live on the <a href="/conformance/">Conformance status</a> page.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="container">
    {% if showcases.length > 0 %}
    {#- Dogfood (#2103, #1607/#1820 Fork 1a): each demo showcase tile is a `<we-card>` frame — the same raw
        card composition the sibling catalog tiles use (blocks.njk, resources.njk). Raw tags (not the #2098
        `weCard` macro) because a demo summary can carry entity-encoded markup (e.g. For-Each's "stamps a
        <template>"); the macro feeds the body through the harness's `innerHTML` round-trip, which DECODES
        `&lt;template&gt;` and leaks a raw tag that swallows the rest of the grid (the documented
        DOM-truncation bug, component-render-build-hook.cjs → renderBacklogGrid). The raw `<we-card>` keeps
        the authored, correctly-escaped body verbatim and upgrades in place client-side (JS-off correct via
        the `we-card{}` style.css baseline). The `<h2 id=demo-…>` anchor + summary + "Uses:" chips +
        `projectStatus` meter stay in the card body. Whole-tile click stays on the OUTER
        `<a class="standard-card">`; `.standard-card:has(> we-card|.fui-card)` strips the anchor's own frame. -#}
    <div class="standards-grid">
        {% for demo in showcases %}
        <a href="/demos/{{ demo.id }}/" class="standard-card" style="text-decoration: none; color: inherit; display: block;">
            <we-card>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-3">
                    <h2 id="demo-{{ demo.id }}" class="text-lg font-bold m-0 text-gray-900">{{ demo.name }}</h2>
                </div>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">{{ demo.summary }}</p>
                {% if demo.projects %}
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Uses:</div>
                    <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: gap; gap: 0.25rem;">
                        {% for projectId in demo.projects %}
                        <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-medium bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 border border-blue-200">
                            {{ projectId }}
                        </span>
                        {% endfor %}
                    </div>
                </div>
                {% endif %}
                <div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                    {{ projectStatus(demo.status) }}
                </div>
            </we-card>
        </a>
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% else %}
    {#- Dogfood (#2103): the empty-state panel is a `<we-card>` content card (raw tag, same rationale as the
        grid tiles above — kept consistent and round-trip-safe). Icon + heading + copy stay in the card body;
        the centered padding chrome the prior `.section-card fui-card` frame carried stays on the anchor-less
        `.standard-card` wrapper, whose frame is stripped by `.standard-card:has(> we-card|.fui-card)`. -#}
    <div class="standard-card" style="text-align: center; padding: 3rem 2rem;">
        <we-card>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="margin: 0 auto 1rem; opacity: 0.3;"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/></svg>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);">No Demos Yet</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); max-width: 500px; margin: 0 auto;">
                Demos are being developed to showcase integrated use cases of Web Everything standards. Check back soon!
            </p>
        </we-card>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
</div>
